<BlogCrossLinks title="How Scrabble Dictionaries Update — SOWPODS & TWL Revision Process" />

<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 6 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The Scrabble dictionary isn't static — it evolves as the English language grows. New words enter through a rigorous vetting process, while controversial terms can be removed. Understanding how this works helps you stay ahead of dictionary changes and anticipate which words might become valid next.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">The Two Major Dictionaries</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
    <p class="text-blue-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">📘 TWL (Tournament Word List)</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Used in North America. ~187,000 words. Managed by NASPA (North American Scrabble Players Association). More conservative with loanwords and informal terms.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
    <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">📗 SOWPODS (Collins Scrabble Words)</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Used internationally. ~279,000 words. Managed by Collins Dictionary editors. More permissive — includes words from all major English dictionaries worldwide.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">279K</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SOWPODS words</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">187K</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWL words</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4-5 yrs</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Update cycle</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">The Update Process Step by Step</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 How a Word Gets Added</p>
  <div class="space-y-3">
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Word appears consistently in published English sources (books, newspapers, academic journals)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Dictionary committee collects citations and evidence of sustained usage over multiple years</p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Committee votes on inclusion — word must meet criteria for established English usage</p>
    </div>
