      <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">4</span>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Accepted words are added to the next edition and announced to the Scrabble community</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">What Gets Words Removed</h2>

<p>Word removal is rare but does happen. The most significant removal event was in 2020 when NASPA removed approximately 236 slurs and offensive terms from the tournament word list.</p>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
    <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚠️ Reasons for Removal</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Offensive or hateful content, words deemed archaic beyond recovery, words entered in error (misspellings or fabrications that slipped through), and trademark issues (proper nouns that were incorrectly included).</p>
